# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Folders and Files to Ignore
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------

# 1. Python Artifacts
# Bytecode and compiled files
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# 2. Dataset (Typically large and should not be version controlled directly)
# Assuming 'dataset' folder contains the raw or processed data
# You might want to remove this line if your dataset is very small and essential.
dataset/

# 4. Environment/Dependency Management
# Virtual environment folders
.venv
venv/
env/

# Dependency files created by some package managers
# If you use Poetry or Conda, you might have specific files to ignore here.
# For pip:
# requirements.txt is usually tracked, but lock files might be ignored
# if they are generated on the fly. We'll keep requirements.txt for tracking.

# 5. Editor and OS Specific Files
# VS Code (The editor shown in the image)
.vscode/

# Operating System files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db